<li><a href="/wiki/H-bridge" title="H-bridge">H-bridge</a> – A topology that combines four switches forming the four legs of an "H". Can be used to drive a motor (or other electrical device) forward or backward when only a single supply is available.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Switching_amplifier" title="Switching amplifier">Switching amplifiers</a> can make use of
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Delta-sigma_modulation" title="Delta-sigma modulation">Delta-sigma modulation</a> – Provides one method of encoding a continuous range of values in a signal that rapidly switches between two states</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Sliding_mode_control" title="Sliding mode control">Sliding mode control</a> – Feedback control scheme (i.e., a kind of generalized <a href="/wiki/Delta-sigma_modulation" title="Delta-sigma modulation">delta-sigma modulation</a>) that uses an output that switches between two states to cause an output to slide along a continuous curve</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Switched-mode_power_supply" title="Switched-mode power supply">Switched-mode power supply</a> – High-efficiency power supply that uses switches and storage elements to trade-off pressure and flow (i.e., voltage and current)</li>
</ul>
